column5:
Electricity day ahead with delivery on the German/Austria TSO zone Underlying: Electricity traded for delivery the following day in 24 hour intervals.

{ALLX EPIG} tracks trades made on an intraday basis for same-day delivery. All trades made on a day-ahead basis are shown on {ALLX EPGA}. On a given day, d, the trades captured by {ALLX EPIG} are comparable to trades captured by {ALLX EPGA} on d-1 for the same time slots.

**A full 25 hour Excel template is needed when the clocks are set to winter time. Hour 3 and 3X can contain different values. When the time is switched to summer time the system automatically deletes the exceeding quantities for hour 3 (i.e. 2.00 am to 3.00am)

The daily auction takes place at 12.00 pm, 7 days a week, year-round, including statutory holidaysDeliveries are made within either of the following TSOs zones (Amprion GmbH,Tennet TSO GmbH,50Hertz Transmission GmbH,EnBW Transportnetze, Austrian Power Grid).

Volume data is available on HP page of the ticker.

{http://www.epexspot.com/en/product-info/auction/germany-austria}

The volume weighted average price for each hourly slot can be calculated by weighting all trades on a given intraday ticker and the corresponding day-ahead ticker on d-1

Bid and Ask values store buy and sell volume respectively. Mid prices store electricity prices.
